sql:
SELECT products.product_name
FROM products
INNER JOIN product_categories ON products.category_id = product_categories.category_id;

external_knowledge:
- "order activities" refers to the number of orders and sales performance metrics;
- "deals they closed" corresponds to the total number of orders;
- "overall earnings from their sales" refers to the total revenue generated;
- "typical sale price" is equivalent to the average order value.

sql:
SELECT oi.order_id, p.product_id, p.product_name, oi.quantity, oi.unit_price, oi.subtotal
FROM order_items oi
JOIN products p ON oi.product_id = p.product_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'treasures hidden in the waters of the past' refers to historical order data;
- 'anchors' metaphorically represent order IDs indicating the stability and identification of orders;
- 'voyages' refer to order statuses indicating the journey or progress of each order;
- 'departure dates' are the created dates of orders;
- 'cargo' represents the physical items or products ordered, signified by item IDs and product IDs;
- 'cargo names' are the names of the products ordered;
- 'cargo volumes' are the quantities of each product;
- 'price per unit' is the unit price, indicating the cost of a single unit of the product;
- 'total cargo value' is calculated as quantity times unit price, which is the subtotal;
- 'discounts offered' is the discount applied to the order item;
- 'storm taxes' represent the tax rate applied to the order item;
- 'sailor' refers to the customer.
